MISSISSIPPI STATE UNIVERSITY HERBARIUM [MISSA]
PLANTS OF ALABAMA

*Galax aphylla* L.
West Fork Little River, trail below lodge at De Soto State Park,
300 m east of De Soto Parkway (County Hwy 89); 34°29.61'N,
85°36.94'W, elev. 430 m.
Canyon slope, mixed-hardwood forest with *Quercus montana*,
*Oxydendron*, *Hamamelis*, *Hydrangea arborescens*, *H. quercifolia*,
*Viburnum acerifolium*, *Kalmia*, *Rhododendron catawbiense*, *Prunus serotina*, *Maianthemum racemosum*,
*Polystichum*, *Dioscorea*, *Asarum shuttleworthii*.
Rhizomatous perennial herb, root orange, petals white, anthers
yellow; common.
12 May 2004
Mark Fishbein #5352, Lane Greer DeKalb County
